    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_720586633" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/720586633" />
    <a title="Jessica Rodrigues ☕ (decafJess)" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/12498816-jessica-rodrigues-decafjess"><img alt="Jessica Rodrigues ☕ (decafJess)" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1641413782p2/12498816.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/720586633?book_show_action=true">Sep 15, 2013</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Jessica Rodrigues ☕ (decafJess)" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Jessica Rodrigues ☕ (decafJess)" href="/user/show/12498816-jessica-rodrigues-decafjess">Jessica Rodrigues ☕ (decafJess)</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="did not like it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">did not like it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/12498816-jessica-rodrigues-decafjess?shelf=sci-fi-fantasy-horror">sci-fi-fantasy-horror</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer720586633" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer4450333104911873154"><b>What just happened?</b><br/><br/>I was so disappointed. I adored <i>A Discovery of Witches</i> and <i>Shadow of Night</i>, but I feel like this book did not tie up any loose ends, answer any questions, or really provide any satisfaction for the build-up of the previous two novels.<br/><br/>A few of my main concerns:<br/><br/><b>Ashmole 782?</b> <a class='jsShowSpoiler spoilerAction'>(view spoiler)</a><span class='spoilerContainer' style='display: none'>[ Why aren&apos;t we told what the book said? Who made the book? Who&apos;s bodies are inside the book? What are their names? Diana promises Timothy to discover their names, but never does. <a class='jsHideSpoiler spoilerAction'>(hide spoiler)</a></span></span>
  <span id="freeText4450333104911873154" style="display:none"><b>What just happened?</b><br /><br />I was so disappointed. I adored <i>A Discovery of Witches</i> and <i>Shadow of Night</i>, but I feel like this book did not tie up any loose ends, answer any questions, or really provide any satisfaction for the build-up of the previous two novels.<br /><br />A few of my main concerns:<br /><br /><b>Ashmole 782?</b> <a class="jsShowSpoiler spoilerAction">(view spoiler)</a><span class="spoilerContainer" style="display: none">[ Why aren't we told what the book said? Who made the book? Who's bodies are inside the book? What are their names? Diana promises Timothy to discover their names, but never does. <a class="jsHideSpoiler spoilerAction">(hide spoiler)</a>]</span><br /><br /><b>Diana and Matthew and the covenant</b> In the first two novels, their love is made out to be some intense taboo a la interracial couples in 1950s Mississippi, but as the novel goes on, no one seems to care. <br /><br /><b>Father Hubbard</b> Is he a good guy or a bad guy? Why are they such jerks to him? He seems like a pretty stand-up guy.<br /><br /><b>Time travel EMT service?</b> <a class="jsShowSpoiler spoilerAction">(view spoiler)</a><span class="spoilerContainer" style="display: none">[Why couldn't they just go back in time and save Diana's parents, Philippe, or Emily? I could see possible butterfly-effect ramifications with her parents or Philippe, but Em had <i>just</i> died. <a class="jsHideSpoiler spoilerAction">(hide spoiler)</a>]</span><br /><br /><b>What was the whole point, anyway?</b> Would this series have ended differently if Diana and Matthew had never discovered Ashmole 782 and had just started dating for the same reasons anyone else starts dating the person they eventually marry?</span>
  <a data-text-id="4450333104911873154" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


