<div id="review_3385128043" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3385128043" />
    <a title="Deborah Obida" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/54790180-deborah-obida"><img alt="Deborah Obida" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1633373489p2/54790180.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3385128043?book_show_action=true">Jul 21, 2020</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Deborah Obida" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Deborah Obida" href="/user/show/54790180-deborah-obida">Deborah Obida</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Kindle Edition " href="/book/show/18815200-the-book-of-life">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/54790180-deborah-obida?shelf=adult">adult</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/54790180-deborah-obida?shelf=urban-fantasy">urban-fantasy</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/54790180-deborah-obida?shelf=romance">romance</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/54790180-deborah-obida?shelf=paranormal">paranormal</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3385128043" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer5906309586470335746">Buddy read with <b>Ruthie</b><br/><br/><b>
  <i>It is not the strongest of the species that survives, nor the most intelligent that survives.<br/> It is the one that is most adaptable to change.</i>
</b><br/><br/>The Book of Life is a good book but a pale conclusion to this series, even though the author concluded most things there were still a few holes that I wish got properly closed. The important part of the book was rushed while the needless unimportant day to day life took way too many page space. Do not even get me started on the way</span>
  <span id="freeText5906309586470335746" style="display:none">Buddy read with <b>Ruthie</b><br /><br /><b>
  <i>It is not the strongest of the species that survives, nor the most intelligent that survives.<br /> It is the one that is most adaptable to change.</i>
</b><br /><br />The Book of Life is a good book but a pale conclusion to this series, even though the author concluded most things there were still a few holes that I wish got properly closed. The important part of the book was rushed while the needless unimportant day to day life took way too many page space. Do not even get me started on the way they dealt with the congregation, Knox and Benjamin, I expected more, the author made them look so strong and powerful then with a snap of a finger they were defeated.<br /><br />Apart from the above points I really enjoyed reading The Book of Life, they finally found the secret of the book. <br /><br /><b>
  <i>“Secrets, like the dead, do not always stay buried,”<br />“But secrets are unreliable allies. They allow us to believe we are safe, yet all the while they are destroying us.”</i>
</b><br /><br />Most of the problems the characters experienced was due to secrets, I'm glad everything came out in the open.<br /><br />The world building is still great, I felt it was underwhelming given how good book two is. Unlike the first and second book this is written in multiple POV which is amazing, I finally got to know what the other characters apart from Diana are thinking.<br /><br />My favourite character is Jack Blackfriars, his reunion with Diana was amazing. I still like Diana, her character development was well done, she no longer acted like the way she did in Shadow of Night, she is more experienced and powerful.<br /><br />Matthew was disappointing here, the author made him almost helpless to make Diana look strong. I wish the author used another method.<br /><br />Chris and Fernando are two new great characters, really enjoyed their parts. The rest of the De Clermont household were also in this.<br /><br />Baldwin is a character that confused me, I still don't know the reasons for why he treated Matthew and Diana the way he did.</span>
  <a data-text-id="5906309586470335746" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


